com.bmwcarit.barefoot.topology

Interface Router<E extends AbstractEdge<E>,P extends Point<E>>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Dijkstra

    public interface Router<E extends AbstractEdge<E>,P extends Point<E>>
    Interface of a router for routing in a directed Graph. The routing functions return paths from a source Point to a target Point that minimize a Cost function.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • route

        List<E> route(P source,
              P target,
              Cost<E> cost)
        Gets path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function.
        Parameters:
        source - Source Point in the graph.
        target - Target Point in the graph.
        cost - Custom Cost function.
        Returns:
        Path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. If there is no path from source to target, it returns null.

      • route

        List<E> route(P source,
              P target,
              Cost<E> cost,
              Cost<E> bound,
              Double max)
        Gets path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. Search depth of routing can be bound by bounding Cost function and a maximum bounding cost value.
        Parameters:
        source - Source Point in the graph.
        target - Target Point in the graph.
        cost - Custom Cost function.
        bound - Bounding Cost function.
        max - Maximum bounding cost value to bound search depth.
        Returns:
        Path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. If there is no path from source to target, it returns null.

      • route

        Map<P,List<E>> route(P source,
                     Set<P> targets,
                     Cost<E> cost)
        Gets path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to each target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function.
        Parameters:
        source - Source Point in the graph.
        targets - Set of target Points in the graph.
        cost - Custom Cost function.
        Returns:
        Map of target Point to path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. If there is no path from source to target, it maps to null.

      • route

        Map<P,List<E>> route(P source,
                     Set<P> targets,
                     Cost<E> cost,
                     Cost<E> bound,
                     Double max)
        Gets path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to each target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. Search depth of routing can be bound by bounding Cost function and a maximum bounding cost value.
        Parameters:
        source - Source Point in the graph.
        targets - Set of target Points in the graph.
        cost - Custom Cost function.
        bound - Bounding Cost function.
        max - Maximum bounding cost value to bound search depth.
        Returns:
        Map of target Point to path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, from source Point to target Point with minimum cost according to Cost function. If there is no path from source to target, it maps to null.

      • route

        Map<P,Tuple<P,List<E>>> route(Set<P> sources,
                              Set<P> targets,
                              Cost<E> cost)
        Gets path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, to each target Point from exactly that source Point that has minimum cost according to Cost function.
        Parameters:
        sources - Set of source Points in the graph.
        targets - Set of target Points in the graph.
        cost - Custom Cost function.
        Returns:
        Map of target Point to a tuple of path, i.e. a sequence of AbstractEdges, and source Point that have minimum cost according to Cost function for reaching the target. If there is no path to target, it maps to null.
